    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 480ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[620ml]</span> [810ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> peanut butter </strong>and your<strong> beef stock mix</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 60 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through – this is your <strong>Gambian-style beef & sweet potato peanut stew</strong></p>",
